sentences: Roni Ben-Hur is an Israeli jazz guitarist who immigrated to the United States in 1985.
He is the youngest of seven children and one of two born after the family emigrated from Tunisia in 1955.
He arrived in New York City in 1985, spending time at Barry Harris's Jazz Cultural Theater.
Ben-Hur's experience as an educator dates back to 1981 in Israel.

His book Talk Jazz: Guitar (Mel Bay, 2004) includes a CD with a removable guitar track of Ben-Hur performing the exercises in the book with Tardo Hammer on piano, Earl May on bass, and Leroy Williams on drums.

His book Talk Jazz: Guitar (Mel Bay, 2004) includes a CD with a removable guitar track of Ben-Hur performing the exercises in the book with Tardo Hammer on piano, Earl May on bass, and Leroy Williams on drums.
His album Anna's Dance was named by The Village Voice one of the best jazz albums of 2001.
In 2000, he won the Jazziz reader poll for "Best New Talent".
